Analysis of the Main Target Image
--------------------------------
• Overall Count and Layers  
  – The model is built from a total of 12 blocks.  
  – It naturally divides into two “sub‐structures”: one on the left featuring arches, a cylinder, and a “roof” wedge, and one on the right featuring four cylinder “columns” with green blocks on top.  
  – The left sub‐structure has its bottom layer of two red arches side by side; above them sits one orange cylinder (with a wedge on top) and, behind it, one tall yellow block and one smaller green block.  
  – The right sub‐structure is two layers: four orange cylinders as the base “columns” and two green rectangular blocks laid side by side forming the top.  

• Spatial Relationships (Left Side)  
  1) Two red arch blocks sit next to each other, forming a double‐arch base.  
  2) Centered on top of the red arches is a single orange cylinder.  
  3) Behind the cylinder are two blocks: one tall yellow rectangular block on the left and one small green rectangular block on the right.  
  4) An orange wedge is placed on top of the vertical cylinder to form a “roof” shape.  

• Spatial Relationships (Right Side)  
  1) Four orange cylinders are arranged in a rectangular footprint (2×2) as the bottom “legs.”  
  2) Two green rectangular blocks lie side by side on top of those cylinders, forming a flat platform.  

Selecting Blocks From the Dictionary
------------------------------------
Below are the blocks (by index) from the dictionary that match exactly in color, shape, and orientation (no re‐orientation allowed). In parentheses is the quantity used.

• Red Arch (index 1) … 2×  
• Orange Cylinder (index 12) … 5× (1 for the left cylinder + 4 for the right columns)  
• Orange Wedge (index 14) … 1× (the “roof” piece on top of the left cylinder)  
• Tall Yellow Rectangular Block (index 10) … 1×  
• Small Green Rectangular Block (index 4) … 1× (behind the cylinder on the left)  
• Green Rectangular Block (index 5) … 2× (the pair forming the top platform on the right)

  Step1:  Move block with index 1
